snippet.textDisplay:
DWP loses court fight over treatment of severely disabled
UK government discriminated against people left worse off by universal credit, say judges.The government has suffered a humiliating court defeat after it was found to have unlawfully discriminated against thousands of severely disabled people who were left financially worse off after moving on to universal credit.

The court of appeal dismissed a challenge by the Department for Work and Pensions to two previous high court decisions that protected claimants in receipt of severe disability premium against a drop in income under the new benefit.The cases were brought by two disabled individuals, known as TP and AR, who had sought justice after their benefit income was reduced by £180 a month when they were required to claim universal credit after moving house into a different local authority area.

Responding to Wednesday’s decision, AR said: “We hope that the court of appeal ruling will finally bring an end to our fight for severely disabled people not to be disadvantaged by universal credit. It is still so shocking to us that we have had to fight so long and so hard just to get the government to see that their policy is unfair.”

Tessa Gregory from the law firm Leigh Day, which represented AR and TP, said the ruling was a “wake-up call” for the DWP.

snippet.textDisplay:
I truly DO hope we can improve Great Britain again the biggest issue is how much we lack in Work Skills i feel utterly powerless myself knowing absolutely nothing, lied to throughout School and used by Colleges especially my local college it was a complete waste of time... i never wanted my life to be stuck working for Shops and Supermarkets but looks like that's how it will go... woopty doo... :\ lol.

I'm a very progressive person, i believe everyone should be given the best opportunities, to learn in the way THEY learn not how some teacher or someone else wants them to, to be given the Practical opportunities rather than mind numbing paperwork all day... every day...written a very confusing way where you can't even be given the time to figure out what you're being confused by or look up other definitions of the same words when YOU DO figure it out, everyone understands things differently and it's something we should start embracing not shaming.

I would LOVE to see Workshops for school students that teach Studying Skills because not very many ppl even know how to write proper Notes these days... i never did... and if you have NO CLUE what to do with the information given then... How can you learn properly? you can't... everything has become about "learning" for the Exam and the Grades but we don't spend our lives doing Exams in our jobs LOL and How can you really Grade knowledge and skills? you can't... Grades mean nothing when we don't have the Skills either.

Take inspiration from Long Beach City College in California their Study Skills Workshops are great they have the videos uploaded here on YouTube too, the one on Note Taking has been totally valuable to me and i'm sad nobody bothers to do this here in The UK but many have said on any videos teaching Note Taking that it was what they needed to organize their work and be able to understand what they're doing. We MUST improve all of this if we hope to create a Productive and Cooperative country.

Do what you want... but allow Scotland to Take Back Control of our Nation.

Thank you for continuing the Austerity. That Election Promise, destroyed within weeks!

Northern Ireland loves how you sold them out, and a couple of hours in Sunderland does nothing for the North of England. HS2 will have no impact for the Northeast. And little offered to Cornwall.

How about providing England with their own devolved Government? Work on that allergy to the Truth that I remember vividly from our shared time at the Oxford Union.

But most of all let Scotland have it’s own say because even Scotland’s Conservatives have come to a realisation that we want to go our own way.

We do not want to slag the rest of the UK with as much excitement of Nigel Farage and Ann Widdecombe (not the best thing to do when you are attempting to negotiate on a Decades’ amount of negotiation in 8 months (27 Members will need time to take whatever deal you attempt to offer and seek the approval of all 27 States for this Brexit Trade Agreement. And be careful of the American President, as he’s a verifiable Liar and his re-election is not even close to a done deal.

So Boris let my Fellow Scots have a Referendum without the Lies you used in our last Referendum. I’m confident that we will be great neighbours.
